<script type="application/ld+json">
{"@context":"https://schema.org","@type":"FAQPage","mainEntity":[{"@type":"Question","name":"How much does it cost to register a Private Limited Company in India?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"Total cost to register a Pvt Ltd company ranges from 7000 to 15000 rupees including MCA fees of around 2000 to 5000, stamp duty varying by state from 1000 to 5000, two DSC certificates at 1500 each, two DIN applications, and name reservation fee. Professional charges for CA or CS assistance range from 5000 to 15000 additionally."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"What is the government fee for company registration on MCA portal?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"MCA government fees include SPICe Plus form filing fee based on authorized capital. For capital up to 1 lakh the fee is around 500 rupees. For 1 to 5 lakh it is 2000. For 5 to 10 lakh it is 5000. Additionally DSC costs 1000 to 1500 per director and name reservation via RUN costs 1000. These are standard MCA portal charges."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"What is the cost of LLP registration in India?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"LLP registration costs approximately 5000 to 10000 rupees including FiLLiP form fees of 500 to 2000 based on contribution, two DPIN applications, two DSC certificates at 1500 each, stamp duty for LLP agreement varying by state, and name reservation. LLP has lower compliance cost than Pvt Ltd with no mandatory audit below 40 lakh turnover."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"What is stamp duty for company registration?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"Stamp duty on MOA and AOA varies significantly by state. Maharashtra charges 0.15 percent of authorized capital with minimum 1000. Delhi charges 0.1 percent. Karnataka charges fixed 500 on each. Tamil Nadu charges 0.3 percent. The stamp duty is paid through the MCA portal during SPICe Plus filing and rates are updated by state governments periodically."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"Is GST registration included in company registration?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"GST registration is free and separate from company registration. However most businesses apply for GST simultaneously. There is no government fee for GST registration. Professional charges for GST application are typically 1000 to 3000. GST is mandatory if turnover exceeds 20 lakh for services or 40 lakh for goods."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"What is the difference between OPC and Pvt Ltd registration cost?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"OPC costs slightly less than Pvt Ltd because it requires only one director and one DSC instead of two. MCA fees are similar. OPC saves approximately 1500 to 3000 on the second DSC and DIN. However OPC has a turnover cap of 2 crore and paid-up capital cap of 50 lakh beyond which it must convert to Pvt Ltd."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"What is DSC and how much does it cost?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"DSC or Digital Signature Certificate is an electronic signature required for MCA filings. Class 3 DSC with 2 year validity costs 1000 to 1500 per person from authorized certifying agencies like eMudhra Sify and nCode. Each director and designated partner needs their own DSC. It is mandatory for all MCA portal filings."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"What is the cost of Partnership Firm registration?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"Partnership firm registration is the cheapest at 1000 to 3000 including registration with Registrar of Firms at 500 to 1000 and stamp duty on partnership deed varying by state. No MCA filing needed. No DSC or DIN required. However partnership has unlimited liability and is not recommended for businesses seeking funding or limited liability protection."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"Can I register a company online in India?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"Yes company registration is fully online through the MCA portal at mca.gov.in using the SPICe Plus form. The process includes name reservation, DSC issuance, DIN allotment, incorporation certificate, PAN and TAN allotment, and EPFO and ESIC registration all through a single integrated form. Typical processing time is 5 to 10 working days."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"What are the annual compliance costs after registration?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"Annual compliance costs include ROC annual filing fees of 2000 to 5000, auditor fees of 10000 to 30000, income tax return filing 5000 to 15000, GST return filing 1000 to 3000 per month, and professional fees. Total annual compliance for a small Pvt Ltd runs 50000 to 150000 depending on transactions and complexity."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"What is authorized capital and how does it affect registration cost?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"Authorized capital is the maximum share capital a company can issue. Higher authorized capital increases MCA filing fees and stamp duty. Most startups begin with 1 lakh authorized capital to minimize costs. It can be increased later by paying additional fees and stamp duty. The paid-up capital can be any amount up to the authorized capital."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"Is Section 8 Company registration free?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"Section 8 or NGO company registration is not free but has reduced government fees. MCA waives the SPICe Plus form fees. However DSC stamp duty and professional charges still apply. Total cost is approximately 5000 to 10000. Section 8 companies get income tax exemption under Section 12A and 80G registration for donors."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"What documents are needed for company registration?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"Key documents include PAN and Aadhaar of all directors, passport size photos, address proof of registered office with NOC from owner, utility bill not older than 2 months, bank statement or telephone bill as address proof of directors, and DSC of all directors. For foreign directors passport copy and notarized documents are additionally required."}}]}
</script>
