<section class="content-section" id="how-to-use"><h2>How to Use the Registration Cost Calculator</h2><p>This tool estimates the total cost of business registration in India based on the latest <a href="https://www.mca.gov.in/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">MCA</a> fee schedule and state-wise stamp duty rates.</p><h3>Step 1 — Select Entity Type</h3><p>Choose from Pvt Ltd, OPC, LLP, Partnership, or Section 8 (NGO). Each has different fee structures and compliance requirements.</p><h3>Step 2 — Select State and Capital</h3><p>State affects stamp duty on MOA/AOA or LLP agreement. Authorized capital affects MCA fees — start with &#8377;1L to minimise initial costs.</p><h3>Step 3 — View Cost Breakup</h3><p>Get detailed line-by-line cost including government fees, stamp duty, DSC, DIN, name reservation, PAN/TAN, and optional professional charges.</p><div class="callout"><p><strong>CA Tip:</strong> Start with &#8377;1 lakh authorized capital to minimise registration cost. You can increase it later as needed. For most startups, Pvt Ltd is recommended for credibility and funding access. LLP suits professional firms with lower compliance overhead. Consult the <a href="https://www.icai.org/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">ICAI</a> for entity selection guidance.</p></div></section>

<section class="content-section" id="comparison"><h2>Business Structure Comparison</h2><div style="overflow-x:auto;"><table class="rate-table"><thead><tr><th>Parameter</th><th>Pvt Ltd</th><th>OPC</th><th>LLP</th><th>Partnership</th></tr></thead><tbody>
<tr><td>Min Members</td><td>2 directors + 2 shareholders</td><td>1 director + 1 nominee</td><td>2 designated partners</td><td>2 partners</td></tr>
<tr><td>Liability</td><td>Limited</td><td>Limited</td><td>Limited</td><td>Unlimited</td></tr>
<tr><td>Compliance</td><td>High (ROC, Audit, AGM)</td><td>Medium</td><td>Low-Medium</td><td>Low</td></tr>
<tr><td>Funding Access</td><td>Best (VC/PE/Angel)</td><td>Limited</td><td>Moderate</td><td>Poor</td></tr>
<tr><td>Typical Cost</td><td>&#8377;7K&ndash;20K</td><td>&#8377;6K&ndash;15K</td><td>&#8377;5K&ndash;12K</td><td>&#8377;1K&ndash;5K</td></tr>
<tr><td>Annual Cost</td><td>&#8377;50K&ndash;1.5L</td><td>&#8377;30K&ndash;80K</td><td>&#8377;10K&ndash;40K</td><td>&#8377;5K&ndash;15K</td></tr>
</tbody></table></div></section>

<section class="content-section" id="fees"><h2>MCA Fee Schedule — 2026</h2><div style="overflow-x:auto;"><table class="rate-table"><thead><tr><th>Fee Component</th><th>Amount</th></tr></thead><tbody>
<tr><td>SPICe+ Form (capital up to &#8377;1L)</td><td>&#8377;500</td></tr>
<tr><td>SPICe+ Form (&#8377;1L&ndash;5L)</td><td>&#8377;2,000</td></tr>
<tr><td>SPICe+ Form (&#8377;5L&ndash;10L)</td><td>&#8377;5,000</td></tr>
<tr><td>SPICe+ Form (&#8377;10L&ndash;50L)</td><td>&#8377;10,000</td></tr>
<tr><td>RUN (Name Reservation)</td><td>&#8377;1,000</td></tr>
<tr><td>DSC (Class 3, 2-year validity)</td><td>&#8377;1,000&ndash;1,500 per person</td></tr>
<tr><td>DIN Application</td><td>&#8377;500 per director</td></tr>
<tr><td>PAN + TAN (via SPICe+)</td><td>Included</td></tr>
<tr><td>FiLLiP (LLP Form)</td><td>&#8377;500&ndash;2,000</td></tr>
</tbody></table></div><p style="font-size:13px;color:var(--text-muted);">Fees as per <a href="https://www.mca.gov.in/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">MCA</a> Companies (Registration Offices and Fees) Rules. Stamp duty varies by state.</p></section>

<section class="content-section" id="startup-exemptions"><h2>Startup India Fee Exemptions & Benefits</h2><p>Businesses recognised under the <a href="https://www.startupindia.gov.in/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Startup India</a> scheme (DPIIT recognition) enjoy significant fee waivers and benefits during registration and early years of operation.</p><ul><li><strong>80% rebate on patent filing fees:</strong> Startups pay only 20% of the standard patent fee, saving &#8377;4,000&ndash;8,000 per application.</li><li><strong>50% rebate on trademark fees:</strong> Reduced from &#8377;9,000 to &#8377;4,500 per trademark application for recognised startups.</li><li><strong>Tax holiday under Section 80-IAC:</strong> 3 consecutive years of 100% tax exemption on profits within the first 10 years of incorporation as per the <a href="https://www.indiacode.nic.in/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Income Tax Act</a>.</li><li><strong>Self-certification for labour and environment laws:</strong> No inspections for 3 years under 6 labour laws and 3 environmental laws.</li><li><strong>Faster winding-up:</strong> Insolvency resolution within 90 days under the Insolvency and Bankruptcy Code.</li></ul><p>To avail these benefits, register your company first and then apply for DPIIT recognition on the Startup India portal with a brief description of your innovation.</p></section>

